      "side": 1,
      "message": "That part is surprising, but maybe it suggests an alternate check, so we keep our conservative initial approach, and then explicitly opt-out of inlining for ANGLE/Chromium.\n\n  if (isES \u0026\u0026 (driver !\u003d kChromium) \u0026\u0026 (driver !\u003d kANGLE))\n\nIt\u0027s possible we never encounter kChromium any more - I think that may only happen with the old command buffer. In any case, I think that set of checks gets us close enough to optimal.",
